&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locality Rapid Response Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AfC Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary £38,890-£44,503 per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Walsall Healthcare NHS Trust is looking to recruit a Locality Rapid Response Nurse with drive and enthusiasm to join one of our integrated community teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the passion to provide high quality holistic case management with strong patient advocacy skills then this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be at the forefront of service development for people with complex long-term conditions who are being cared for in the Community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require extensive experience as a senior clinician and need to demonstrate clinical competence in delivering rapid response care to patients with complex needs and preventing hospital admissions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have skills in advanced health assessment and Independent prescribing for this role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide clinical training and mentorship support for the role and you will be required to undertake further development to enhance your knowledge and skills including extended nurse prescribing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Walsall Healthcare NHS Trust’s Community nursing service is striving to continually improve care pathways for patients, their carer’s and families. We therefore work closely with our colleagues across primary, secondary and social care organisations to ensure that the care we deliver is continuous and puts our patients at the center of the care provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKay CrowtherJob titleClinical LeadEmail addresskay.crowther@walsallhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number01922 605768Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;in the absence of Kay Crowther please contact Deb Watson on Debbie.Watson@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
